`.\n\n- For example, `\"00010\" -> \"00001\"`\n\n*Return the **maximum binary string** you can obtain after any number of operations. Binary string `x` is greater than binary string `y` if `x`'s decimal representation is greater than `y`'s decimal representation.*\n\n**Example 1:**\n\nInput: binary = \"000110\"\nOutput: \"111011\"\nExplanation: A valid transformation sequence can be:\n\"000110\" -> \"000101\" \n\"000101\" -> \"100101\" \n\"100101\" -> \"110101\" \n\"110101\" -> \"110011\" \n\"110011\" -> \"111011\"\n\n**Example 2:**\n\nInput: binary = \"01\"\nOutput: \"01\"\nExplanation: \"01\" cannot be transformed any further.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= binary.length <= 10⁵`\n\n- `binary` consist of `'0'` and `'1'`.","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/maximum-binary-string-after-change/","problemName":"Maximum Binary String After Change","problemNumber":1702,"problemSlug":"maximum-binary-string-after-change","schemaVersion":2,"sequenceIndex":1702,"solutionApproaches":[]},{"assets":[],"categories":["Array","Greedy","Sliding Window","Prefix Sum"],"constraintBlocks":[],"contentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"You are given an integer array, `nums`, and an integer `k`. `nums` comprises of only `0`'s and `1`'s. In one move, you can choose two **adjacent** indices and swap their values.\n\nReturn *the **minimum** number of moves required so that *`nums`* has *`k`* **consecutive** *`1`*'s*.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input: nums = [1,0,0,1,0,1], k = 2\nOutput: 1\nExplanation: In 1 move, nums could be [1,0,0,0,1,1] and have 2 consecutive 1's.","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: nums = [1,0,0,0,0,0,1,1], k = 3\nOutput: 5\nExplanation: In 5 moves, the leftmost 1 can be shifted right until nums = [0,0,0,0,0,1,1,1].","type":"code"},{"sequence":4,"text":"**Example 3:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":5,"text":"Input: nums = [1,1,0,1], k = 2\nOutput: 0\nExplanation: nums already has 2 consecutive 1's.","type":"code"},{"sequence":6,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= nums.length <= 10⁵`\n\n- `nums[i]` is `0` or `1`.\n\n- `1 <= k <= sum(nums)`","type":"text"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["Array","Greedy","Sliding Window","Prefix Sum"],"createdAt":0,"difficulty":"Hard","lastRevisionAt":0,"problem":"You are given an integer array, `nums`, and an integer `k`. `nums` comprises of only `0`'s and `1`'s. In one move, you can choose two **adjacent** indices and swap their values.\n\nReturn *the **minimum** number of moves required so that *`nums`* has *`k`* **consecutive** *`1`*'s*.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\nInput: nums = [1,0,0,1,0,1], k = 2\nOutput: 1\nExplanation: In 1 move, nums could be [1,0,0,0,1,1] and have 2 consecutive 1's.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\nInput: nums = [1,0,0,0,0,0,1,1], k = 3\nOutput: 5\nExplanation: In 5 moves, the leftmost 1 can be shifted right until nums = [0,0,0,0,0,1,1,1].\n\n**Example 3:**\n\nInput: nums = [1,1,0,1], k = 2\nOutput: 0\nExplanation: nums already has 2 consecutive 1's.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= nums.length <= 10⁵`\n\n- `nums[i]` is `0` or `1`.\n\n- `1 <= k <= sum(nums)`","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/minimum-adjacent-swaps-for-k-consecutive-ones/","problemName":"Minimum Adjacent Swaps for K Consecutive Ones","problemNumber":1703,"revisionAnchorAt":0,"revisionCount":0,"revisionDates":[],"revisionPlanHours":[1,24,168,336,672],"solutionCode":"","testCases":"","updatedAt":0},"descriptionBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"You are given an integer array, `nums`, and an integer `k`. `nums` comprises of only `0`'s and `1`'s. In one move, you can choose two **adjacent** indices and swap their values.\n\nReturn *the **minimum** number of moves required so that *`nums`* has *`k`* **consecutive** *`1`*'s*.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input: nums = [1,0,0,1,0,1], k = 2\nOutput: 1\nExplanation: In 1 move, nums could be [1,0,0,0,1,1] and have 2 conse