 is between dates 2020-11-11 and 2021-1-1 with a total of 51 days.","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/biggest-window-between-visits/","problemName":"Biggest Window Between Visits","problemNumber":1709,"problemSlug":"biggest-window-between-visits","schemaVersion":2,"sequenceIndex":1709,"solutionApproaches":[]},{"assets":[],"categories":["Array","Greedy","Sorting"],"constraintBlocks":[],"contentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"You are assigned to put some amount of boxes onto **one truck**. You are given a 2D array `boxTypes`, where `boxTypes[i] = [numberOfBoxesi, numberOfUnitsPerBoxi]`:\n\n- `numberOfBoxesi` is the number of boxes of type `i`.\n\n- `numberOfUnitsPerBoxi` is the number of units in each box of the type `i`.\n\nYou are also given an integer `truckSize`, which is the **maximum** number of **boxes** that can be put on the truck. You can choose any boxes to put on the truck as long as the number of boxes does not exceed `truckSize`.\n\nReturn *the **maximum** total number of **units** that can be put on the truck.*\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input: boxTypes = [[1,3],[2,2],[3,1]], truckSize = 4\nOutput: 8\nExplanation: There are:\n- 1 box of the first type that contains 3 units.\n- 2 boxes of the second type that contain 2 units each.\n- 3 boxes of the third type that contain 1 unit each.\nYou can take all the boxes of the first and second types, and one box of the third type.\nThe total number of units will be = (1 * 3) + (2 * 2) + (1 * 1) = 8.","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: boxTypes = [[5,10],[2,5],[4,7],[3,9]], truckSize = 10\nOutput: 91","type":"code"},{"sequence":4,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= boxTypes.length <= 1000`\n\n- `1 <= numberOfBoxesi, numberOfUnitsPerBoxi <= 1000`\n\n- `1 <= truckSize <= 10⁶`","type":"text"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["Array","Greedy","Sorting"],"createdAt":0,"difficulty":