\" + \"bcb\" + \"dd\", and all three substrings are palindromes.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\nInput: s = \"bcbddxy\"\nOutput: false\nExplanation: s cannot be split into 3 palindromes.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `3 <= s.length <= 2000`\n\n- `s` consists only of lowercase English letters.","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/palindrome-partitioning-iv/","problemName":"Palindrome Partitioning IV","problemNumber":1745,"problemSlug":"palindrome-partitioning-iv","schemaVersion":2,"sequenceIndex":1745,"solutionApproaches":[]},{"assets":[],"categories":["Array","Dynamic Programming"],"constraintBlocks":[],"contentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"You are given an integer array `nums`. You must perform **exactly one** operation where you can **replace** one element `nums[i]` with `nums[i] * nums[i]`.\n\nReturn *the **maximum** possible subarray sum after **exactly one** operation*. The subarray must be non-empty.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input: nums = [2,-1,-4,-3]\n\nOutput: 17\n\nExplanation: You can perform the operation on index 2 (0-indexed) to make nums = [2,-1,16,-3]. Now, the maximum subarray sum is 2 + -1 + 16 = 17.","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: nums = [1,-1,1,1,-1,-1,1]\n\nOutput: 4\n\nExplanation: You can perform the operation on index 1 (0-indexed) to make nums = [1,1,1,1,-1,-1,1]. Now, the maximum subarray sum is 1 + 1 + 1 + 1 = 4.","type":"code"},{"sequence":4,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= nums.length <= 10⁵`\n\n- `-10⁴ <= nums[i] <= 10⁴`","type":"text"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["Array","Dynamic Programming"],"createdAt":0,"difficulty":"Medium","lastRevisionAt":0,"problem":"You are given an integer array `nums`. You must perform **exactly one** operation where you can **replace** one element `nums[i]` with `nums[i] * nums[i]`.\n\nReturn *the **maximum** possible subarray sum after **exactly one** operation*. The subarray must be non-empty.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\nInput: nums = [2,-1,-4,-3]\n\nOutput: 17\n\nExplanation: You can perform the operation on index 2 (0-indexed) to make nums = [2,-1,16,-3]. Now, the maximum subarray sum is 2 + -1 + 16 = 17.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\nInput: nums = [1,-1,1,1,-1,-1,1]\n\nOutput: 4\n\nExplanation: You can perform the operation on index 1 (0-indexed) to make nums = [1,1,1,1,-1,-1,1]. Now, the maximum subarray sum is 1 + 1 + 1 + 1 = 4.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= nums.length <= 10⁵`\n\n- `-10⁴ <= nums[i] <= 10⁴`","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/maximum-subarray-sum-after-one-operation/","problemName":"Maximum Subarray Sum After One Operation","problemNumber":1746,"revisionAnchorAt":0,"revisionCount":0,"revisionDates":[],"revisionPlanHours":[1,24,168,336,672],"solutionCode":"","testCases":"","updatedAt":0},"descriptionBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"You are given an integer array `nums`. You must perform **exactly one** operation where you can **replace** one element `nums[i]` with `nums[i] * nums[i]`.\n\nReturn *the **maximum** possible subarray sum after **exactly one** operation*. The subarray must be non-empty.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input: nums = [2,-1,-4,-3]\n\nOutput: 17\n\nExplanation: You can perform the operation on index 2 (0-indexed) to make nums = [2,-1,16,-3]. Now, the maximum subarray sum is 2 + -1 + 16 = 17.","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: nums = [1,-1,1,1,-1,-1,1]\n\nOutput: 4\n\nExplanation: You can perform the operation on index 1 (0-indexed) to make nums = [1,1,1,1,-1,-1,1]. Now, the maximum subarray sum is 1 + 1 + 1 + 1 = 4.","type":"code"},{"sequence":4,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= nums.length <= 10⁵`\n\n- `-10⁴ <= nums[i] <= 10⁴`","type":"text"}],"difficulty":"Medium","examples":[],"paidOnly":false,"problem":"You are given an integer array `nums`. You must perform **exactly one** operation where you can **replace** one element `nums[i]` with `nums[i] * nums[i]`.\n\nReturn *the **maximum** possible subarray sum after **exactly one** operation*. The subarray must be non-empty.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\nInput: nums = [2,-1,-4,-3]\n\nOutput: 17\n\nExplanation: You can perform the operation on index 2 (0-indexed) to make nums = [2,-1,16,-3]. Now, the maximum subarray sum is 2 + -1 + 16 = 17.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\nInput: nums = [1,-1,1,1,-1,-1,1]\n\nOutput: 4\n\nExplanation: You can perform the operation on index 1 (0-indexed) to make nums = [1,1,1,1,-1,-1,1]. Now, the maximum subarray sum is 1 + 1 + 1 + 1 = 4.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= nums.length <= 10⁵`\n\n- `-10⁴ <= nums[i] <= 10⁴`","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/maximum-subarray-sum-after-one-operation/","problemName":"Maximum Subarray Sum After One Operation","problemNumber":1746,"problemSlug":"maximum-subarray-sum-after-one-operation","schemaVersion":2,"sequenceIndex":1746,"solutionApproaches":[]},{"assets":[],"categories":["Database"],"constraintBlocks":[],"contentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"Table: `LogInfo`","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"+-------------+----------+\n| Column Name | Type     |\n+-------------+----------+\n| account_id  | int      |\n| ip_address  | int      |\n| login       | datetime |\n| logout      | datetime |\n+-------------+----------+\nThis table may contain duplicate rows.\nThe table contains information about the login and logout dates of Leetflex accounts. It also contains the IP address from which the account was logged in and out.\nIt is guaranteed that the logout time is after the login time.","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"Write a solution to find the `account_id` of the accounts that should be banned from Leetflex. An account should be banned if it was logged in at some moment from two different IP addresses.\n\nReturn the result table in **any order**.\n\nThe result format is in the following example.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"In