 3, goal = -4\nOutput: 2\nExplanation: You can add -2 and -3, then the sum of the array will be 1 - 1 + 1 - 2 - 3 = -4.","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: nums = [1,-10,9,1], limit = 100, goal = 0\nOutput: 1","type":"code"},{"sequence":4,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= nums.length <= 10⁵`\n\n- `1 <= limit <= 10⁶`\n\n- `-limit <= nums[i] <= limit`\n\n- `-10⁹ <= goal <= 10⁹`","type":"text"}],"difficulty":"Medium","examples":[],"paidOnly":false,"problem":"You are given an integer array `nums` and two integers `limit` and `goal`. The array `nums` has an interesting property that `abs(nums[i]) <= limit`.\n\nReturn *the minimum number of elements you need to add to make the sum of the array equal to *`goal`. The array must maintain its property that `abs(nums[i]) <= limit`.\n\nNote that `abs(x)` equals `x` if `x >= 0`, and `-x` otherwise.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\nInput: nums = [1,-1,1], limit = 3, goal = -4\nOutput: 2\nExplanation: You can add -2 and -3, then the sum of the array will be 1 - 1 + 1 - 2 - 3 = -4.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\nInput: nums = [1,-10,9,1], limit = 100, goal = 0\nOutput: 1\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= nums.length <= 10⁵`\n\n- `1 <= limit <= 10⁶`\n\n- `-limit <= nums[i] <= limit`\n\n- `-10⁹ <= goal <= 10⁹`","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/minimum-elements-to-add-to-form-a-given-sum/","problemName":"Minimum Elements to Add to Form a Given Sum","problemNumber":1785,"problemSlug":"minimum-elements-to-add-to-form-a-given-sum","schemaVersion":2,"sequenceIndex":1785,"solutionApproaches":[]},{"assets":[{"assetIndex":0,"bytes":26737,"contentType":"image/png","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/1786-number-of-restricted-paths-from-first-to-last-node/1786-restricted_paths_ex1.png","originalUrl":"../../../images/1786-restricted_paths_ex1.png","sha256":"3604fafda950f701c20117dd69f95710354fc0af2e24a9165a5dc6c16f88d637"},{"assetIndex":1,"bytes":33718,"contentType":"image/png","localPat