ntentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"You are given two strings `firstString` and `secondString` that are **0-indexed** and consist only of lowercase English letters. Count the number of index quadruples `(i,j,a,b)` that satisfy the following conditions:\n\n- `0 <= i <= j < firstString.length`\n\n- `0 <= a <= b < secondString.length`\n\n- The substring of `firstString` that starts at the `i^(th)` character and ends at the `j^(th)` character (inclusive) is **equal** to the substring of `secondString` that starts at the `a^(th)` character and ends at the `b^(th)` character (inclusive).\n\n- `j - a` is the **minimum** possible value among all quadruples that satisfy the previous conditions.\n\nReturn *the **number** of such quadruples*.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input: firstString = \"abcd\", secondString = \"bccda\"\nOutput: 1\nExplanation: The quadruple (0,0,4,4) is the only one that satisfies all the conditions and minimizes j - a.","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: firstString = \"ab\", secondString = \"cd\"\nOutput: 0\nExplanation: There are no quadruples satisfying all the conditions.","type":"code"},{"sequence":4,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= firstString.length, secondString.length <= 2 * 10⁵`\n\n- Both strings consist only of lowercase English letters.","type":"text"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["Greedy","Hash Table","String"],"createdAt":0,"difficulty":"Medium","lastRevisionAt":0,"problem":"You are given two strings `firstString` and `secondString` that are **0-indexed** and consist only of lowercase English letters. Count the number of index quadruples `(i,j,a,b)` that satisfy the following conditions:\n\n- `0 <= i <= j < firstString.length`\n\n- `0 <= a <= b < secondString.length`\n\n- The substring of `firstString` that starts at the `i^(th)` character and ends at the `j^(th)` character (inclusive) is **equal** to the s